com.spazedog.lib.rootfw3.extenders

Class ShellExtender

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.spazedog.lib.rootfw3.extenders.ShellExtender
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ExtenderGroup

    public class ShellExtender
extends java.lang.Object
implements ExtenderGroup
    This class is used to communicate with the shell.
    As this class is an extender, is should not be called directly. Instead use RootFW.shell()
    Example:
     RootFW root = new RootFW();
 
 if (root.isConnected()) {
     ShellResult result = root.shell().addCommands("command1", "command2").run();
     
     if (result.wasSuccessfull) {
         String lastLine = result.line();
     }
     
     root.disconnect();
 }

    • Method Detail

      • buildCommands

        public ShellExtender buildCommands(java.lang.String... commands)
        This is the same as addCommands(), only this one will auto create multiple attempts using each defined binary in RootFW.Config.BINARY. You can use the prefix %binary to represent where the binary should be injected.
        For an example, if you add the command buildCommands('%binary df -h'), this method will create new String[]{'busybox df -h', 'toolbox df -h', 'df -h'}. This makes it easier to add multiple attempts without having to type in each attempt via addCommands().
        Parameters:
        commands - A string containing a command with %binary prefix
        Returns:
        This instance

      • buildCommands

        public ShellExtender buildCommands(java.lang.String[]... commands)
        This is the same as buildCommands().
        If you add the command buildCommands(new String[]{'%binary df -h', '%binary df'}), this method will create new String[]{'busybox df -h', 'toolbox df -h', 'df -h', 'busybox df', 'toolbox df', 'df'}.
        Parameters:
        commands - An array containing multiple attempts with %binary prefix
        Returns:
        This instance

      • addCommands

        public ShellExtender addCommands(java.lang.String... commands)
        This is used to add multiple commands to be executed in the shell. Each argument should be a separate command to be executed. Each command output will be merged in the ShellResult.
        If one command fails (Does not return a valid result code), it will stop executing the rest of the commands.
        Parameters:
        commands - A string containing a command
        Returns:
        This instance

      • addCommands

        public ShellExtender addCommands(java.lang.String[]... commands)
        This is used to add multiple commands with multiple attempt in each. Each array is treated as one command, the class will execute each item in the array until one is successful, after which it will continue to the next argument. Only the output from each successful array item is returned in the ShellResult.
        Parameters:
        commands - An array with multiple attempts of the same command
        Returns:
        This instance

      • setResultCodes

        public ShellExtender setResultCodes(java.lang.Integer... result)
        Whether or not a command was successful or not, depends on the result code returned by the shell. This result code determines the result of ShellResult.wasSuccessfull() and it also controls when to stop executing multiple command attempts.
        By default, 0 is considered successful, but you might need other result codes to be considered successful as well. This method allows you to add more result codes to be considered successful.
        Parameters:
        result - A result code to be considered successful
        Returns:
        This instance

      • reset

        public ShellExtender reset()
        Whenever you add commands using builtCommands() and addCommands(), or adds more result codes via setResultCodes(), this is all cached until you execute run().
        This method will reset this cache without having to execute run().
        Returns:
        This instance

      • run

        public ShellExtender.ShellResult run()
        This method will execute all of the commands that has been added via addCommands() and builtCommands().
        Returns:
        a new instance of ShellResult with all of the shell output and information like the result code.

      • run

        public ShellExtender.ShellResult run(java.lang.String command)
        This method allows you to directly execute one single command without having to use addCommands() and builtCommands().
        Note that if you have already used addCommands() or builtCommands(), this argument will just be added to the stack. It does not reset anything before executing.
        Parameters:
        command - One single command to be executed in the shell
        Returns:
        a new instance of ShellResult with all of the shell output and information like the result code.
